title: "Introducing Climatelag: A Computational Framework for Environmental/Climate Economics"
authors:
  - name: "Economic Research Collective"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-02-17"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/EconomicTermDevelopments/climatelag-economics"
keywords:
  - economics
  - climatelag
  - environmental/climate-economics
  - computational-framework
  - emerging-terminology
abstract: "Climatelag is defined here as temporal delay between greenhouse gas emissions and resulting climate impacts creating intertemporal externalities. This paper develops Climatelag as a computational framework for environmental/climate economics by linking the concept to intertemporal delay between emissions and realized climate damages, formalizing carbon stock persistence and slow system response creating delayed but committed impacts, and operationalizing Climatelag with a transparent index built from channels such as emission flow, atmospheric stock, response delay, and damage realization lag, while also showing how Climatelag can support comparative statics, empirical measurement, and policy simulation in reproducible economic research."
